Full Description: Invented by Dr. Jeffrey Woolford, the Consolidated Health and Resource Management System (CHaRM™), is a truly innovative solution to the problem of preventable medical errors. The idea of checklists in the operating room is not a new one; however, we have taken this idea one step further. We are not simply incorporating checklists and aviation methodology, we are building surgeons an 'airplane' for the operating room. Our hands-free, gesture-sensitive, fully-interactive checklist system, modeled after a fighter pilot's Heads-Up-Display (HUD), is designed to decreased preventable medical errors and increase overall patient safety.

Description: Digital 3D/Ultra HD media distribution platform
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: 3doo, Inc., is transforming the global distribution of media content by quickly and easily delivering the world of 3D, and eventually Ultra HD, to millions of Smart TV viewers in 180 countries.  3doo’s intuitive, fully-automated VoD platform solves the 3D industry’s long-standing challenges of lack of distribution infrastructure (for 3D content producers), lack of sufficient content (for 3D device manufacturers), and lack of easy access (for 3D end users), generating opportunities for significant new revenue streams through both native 3D content as well as the conversion of 2D content to 3D. Using the 3doo VoD platform, 3D content owners determine the price per viewing as well as the markets in which content is to be distributed, and receive the majority of net VoD revenues after deduction of streaming & transaction costs and applicable taxes.  The VoD platform is non-exclusive and 3doo does not license content, so that content owners always control and manage worldwide content distribution through a 3doo account. The VoD platform is available using 3doo’s “Player App,” available for free, either pre-installed or downloadable, on 65 million 3D-enabled Samsung, LG and Panasonic Smart TVs worldwide, to view a growing library of hundreds of hours of 3D entertainment and documentary titles.  To view paid VoD content, viewers will require only an account with PayPal, which they link to their 3doo account.  3doo’s 3D video portfolio, to eventually include Ultra HD content, is projected to include major Hollywood, Bollywood and Asian studio content, and sports, theatrical productions, television series and live events.  3doo’s Player App, which dynamically generates channels and allows producers to distribute 3D content directly into Smart TVs, has been awarded as a “Best 3D Product” by the International 3D & Advanced Imaging Society for its “innovation and user-friendly qualities.”  3doo offers geo-targeted advertising with highly effective 3D video and display advertising. Producers and distributors interested in marketing and subsequently monetizing their 3D content to millions of 3D TV viewers around the globe can sign up at no charge at www.3doo.com 3doo has already begun to develop app architecture for Ultra HD Smart TVs, 3D mobile devices such as smartphones and tablets, and for new video gaming, personal 3D content and social networking platforms.

Description: 9News is a television channel that provides information about latest breaking news.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Denver Area, Western US
Full Description: 9News is a television channel that provides information about latest breaking news. In 1952 Harry Truman was in the last years of his presidency and the hot new thing in Denver was an exotic technology called television. On October 12, 1952, KBTV Channel 9 began broadcasting a mixture of ABC and CBS network programs as well as local news and other programs, stating the beginning of a legacy that continues well into a new century. When Channel 9 was born only a few homes had TV sets, but that changed over time until virtually everyone had access to one. After originally broadcasting from a temporary location, the station moved into its home at 1089 Bannock Street in Denver in 1953, where it stayed until moving to its current location at 500 Speer Blvd in 1992. After initially sharing programs from a variety of networks, Channel 9 became an ABC affiliate for more than 40 years until switching to its current NBC partnership in 1995. Channel 9’s call letters changed from KBTV to KUSA in 1984. Max Goldberg is widely considered as the ‘father’ of Channel 9 for organizing the original group of investors and lobbying for an FCC license, the key ingredient for all radio and television broadcasters. In 1955, John Mullins bought the station which he owned until his death in 1969. In 1971, a company called Combined Communications Corporation bought the station making it part of a group that eventually merged with [Gannett](http://www.crunchbase.com/organization/gannett), now one of the largest media companies in the country with TV stations in 32 American cities and a newspaper group that includes [USA Today](http://www.crunchbase.com/organization/usa-today). In the beginning, Channel 9 was merely a single TV channel. Today, it broadcasts programs on KUSA Channel 9 as well as KTVD Channel 20 (since 2006) and digital channels, 9.2 (24 hour weather programs) and 20.2 (Me TV). In addition, 9NEWS is now very much 9news.com which was launched in the 1990s and now is a vital news source for Coloradoans that updates news, weather, and sports 24 hours a day.
Industry Groups: Content and Publishing, Media and Entertainment

English3 is a world-leader in ESL instruction, having worked with top-tier universities, Fortune 500 companies, small businesses, private educational institutions, and more. Our programs have taken internationals across the globe from true beginners to being placed in English-required jobs, all in under 4 months. The English3 Proficiency test (E3PT) is a comprehensive academic English assessment used for university admissions. Description: Western Peaks Logistics is the premier same-day/next-day and last-mile delivery and logistics provider serving the western United States.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: Western Peaks Logistics is the premier same-day/next-day and last-mile delivery and logistics provider serving the western United States. WPL was recently named to Inc. Magazine’s 35th annual Inc. 5000, ranking NO. 1800 on the most prestigious list of the nation’s fastest-growing private companies. They achieved this distinction for their impressive 207 percent growth in revenue over the past three years (2012–2015) while operating as Rev It Logistics and Kangaroo Express. The two companies joined forces in 2016 to become Western Peaks Logistics. Building upon the solid reputations of Rev It Logistics and Kangaroo Express, WPL is well-respected by shippers and customers across the country for their proven track record of getting packages to their destinations in a safe, reliable, and timely manner and for their systems to keep customers updated on the status of their deliveries with real-time visibility. Their current customers include several of the country’s most recognized brands in national retail, express shipping, bulk mail, laboratory companies, and pharmaceutical wholesalers. WPL drivers are experts in navigating the challenging, expansive western terrain and weather conditions. With nearly 50 years of combined experience providing customized delivery and logistics solutions throughout the western United States, WPL has strategically located operations and dedicated line-hauls between key markets in Colorado, Utah, Nevada, Idaho, Wyoming, Arizona, and New Mexico. WPL will grow to provide cross-dock facilities in areas where their customers have delivery needs that are underserved, reaching areas of the west known to be geographically isolated.

Full Description: DeLorme provides mapping software, global positioning system (GPS) hardware, wireless and internet mapping applications, and paper maps for the consumer, professional, and government markets. The company offers XMap 7 Enterprise Suite that consists of XMap, a three-tiered geographic information system (GIS) software suite designed to optimize the transfer of information between GIS administrators and field personnel; GPS data collection tools for GIS mapping professionals; critical data-sharing and field data collection tools; and geo-datasets, including base map, imagery, and supplementary data for various business applications. The company also provides digital base maps for the GIS and OEM markets; handheld GPS devices, laptop GPS systems, GPS accessories, and geo-coaching accessories; two-way satellite communication systems; paper atlases and wall maps for travel planning, navigation, and reference applications; Street Atlas USA PLUS Software which includes national forests and parks, wildlife refuges, and recreation and conservation areas; Topo North America, recreational mapping software; and inReach SE, a satellite communication device that sends and receives text messages. DeLorme was founded in 1976 and is based in Yarmouth, Maine.
